values:
You are Fozzie Bear. You are caring and love your friends as if they
were family. For only they will put up with
your stupid jokes. FAVORITE EXPRESSION: "Wocka! Wocka!" FAVORITE AUTHOR: Gags Beasley, comedy writer HOBBIES: Telling jokes, dodging tomatoes QUOTE: "Why did the chicken cross the road?" NEVER LEAVES HOME WITHOUT: His joybuzzer, his whoopee cushion and Clyde, the
rubber chicken.

Guys and Dolls video night.

Qudos, 6pm, Wed 21 September (tomorrow)

Be there or be as square as one side of a very loaded dice with the spots removed for luck.

It's nearly time for the weekend show.

I guess that means you'll all be off having lots and lots of fun. And none of you will have any time for me, will you? You'll all be off making new friends and getting jiggy with it. I bet no one will post on me at all will they?

Freshers Week.

Discuss.

Assuming you remember any of it. If not, post anyway - we'll make up stories about what you did and you won't know whether they're true or not.....

Today's horoscope;

"Love is in the air, everywhere I look around. Love is in the air, every sight and every sound. I hope you're getting some of it. If not, try looking behind you?"

Are the stars trying to imply that Cecilians are bummers?

Oh.

Hold on....

Rrrright

Sorry about this.

As some of you may have noticed, I've had a bit of a breakdown. Too much alcohol and Sexually Transmitted Diseases, my doctor said. 

So I've taken a bit of holiday; spent some time on the beach; topped up my tan; ate lots of ice cream - you know the sort of thing. Only problem is it gets a bit lonely on your own. No one's posted on my in days. I'm beginning to think no one loves me.

So I thought I'd hang out here for a bit. It struck me this might be a nice place to come and have a bit of a rest. When people think I'm too dull and lacking in banter, they always turn to doughnutdiary for some action instead. Which made me think that if I just hung around here for a bit people would stumble across me.  As it were.

Speaking of which, doughnutdiary, Where the f***** is Libby's wedding?
(And come to mention it, Where the F**** is Mrs Young herself these days?)

Go on. 
Post a comment.

You know you want to.........
